issue.title: pp_file_not_found | cmake + compile_commands.json + clangd sometimes bugs when finding STATIC library linked to an INTERFACE library
issue.body:
- I have a minimal game engine project at https://github.com/somedeveloper00/HelloWorld/tree/a77f02d (don't forget `--recursive` if wanted to troubleshoot) 
- I'm using CMAKE along with the `compile_commands.json` file autogenerated by CMAKE. (all the codes available in the above link. It's very basic, just a root cmake file and a few projects in directories)
- I use the latest version of the vscode extension https://github.com/clangd/vscode-clangd
- The issue arises on any file using the `glad` and the `glm` headers. clangd simply doesn't recognize these headers and errors `pp_file_not_found`, even though they build and compile fine.

**Logs**
it's in the repo commit I linked above. at https://github.com/somedeveloper00/HelloWorld/blob/a77f02db3bb608be543ef51c993fed06dcfca7cd/clang-logs.txt (because it was too long to put in this text box)

**System information**
Output of `clangd --version`:
```
clangd version 20.1.8 (https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project 87f0227cb60147a26a1eeb4fb06e3b505e9c7261)
Features: windows+grpc
Platform: x86_64-pc-windows-msvc
```
Editor/LSP plugin:
https://github.com/clangd/vscode-clangd

Operating system:
Windows 11

comment.body:
The solution was to add a `dummy.cpp` and link it to the `INTERFACE` library with `target_sources`. This adds the following entry to the json:
```json
{
  "directory": "E:/source/GameEngine/build",
  "command": "C:\\PROGRA~1\\MICROS~4\\2022\\Preview\\VC\\Tools\\MSVC\\1444~1.352\\bin\\Hostx64\\x64\\cl.exe  /nologo /TP -IE:\\source\\GameEngine\\windows\\include -IE:\\source\\GameEngine\\engine\\include -IE:\\source\\GameEngine\\vendors\\glad\\include -IE:\\source\\GameEngine\\vendors\\glm -IE:\\source\\GameEngine\\vendors\\glfw\\include /DWIN32 /D_WINDOWS /EHsc /Ob0 /Od -std:c++20 -MDd -RTC1 -Zi @windows\\CMakeFiles\\windows.dir\\__\\engine\\src\\dummy.cpp.obj.modmap /Fowindows\\CMakeFiles\\windows.dir\\__\\engine\\src\\dummy.cpp.obj /Fdwindows\\CMakeFiles\\windows.dir\\ /FS -c E:\\source\\GameEngine\\engine\\src\\dummy.cpp",
  "file": "E:\\source\\GameEngine\\engine\\src\\dummy.cpp",
  "output": "windows\\CMakeFiles\\windows.dir\\__\\engine\\src\\dummy.cpp.obj"
}
```
I still think this issue was a clangd bug because I already had an entry containing the same entries as above, and Microsoft's C++ intellisense didn't have an issue either. Which is why I'm not closing this issue with this comment.

issue.title: Fix: clear duplicate-casing errors after case-only file renames on Windows (closes #261995)
issue.body: On case-insensitive file systems (Windows for example) renaming a file by only changing its letter-case ~ for example `page1.js` => `Page1.js` ~ confuses `tsserver`. It continues to hold both casings in the program and surfaces errors such as: The error persists until the user manually restarts the TS server or reloads VS Code (see bug #261995). ### RCA File-watcher stacks don‚Äôt always emit a delete => create sequence for a case-only rename on case-insensitive FSs. `tsserver` therefore never drops the old path and thinks the file is duplicated. ### Testing * Verified on Windows 11. ### Files changed * `extensions/typescript-language-features/src/languageFeatures/updatePathsOnRename.ts` * `extensions/typescript-language-features/src/typeScriptServiceClientHost.ts` --- Closes #261995
